node.text:
Getting our @ironmaiden on with the best guitar teacher ever @inmybookofspells 🤘🏼and our @officialjacksonguitars 

Brett has been an inspiration in my life since the first years I picked up a guitar. We grew up going to the same schools since grade 1. It wasn’t until I was in high school when we became friends and shared the same love for metal and guitar. 

Brett’s band Nephilim was one of my first real local concerts I’d been to. I almost never missed and show and they were prodigies for their age. It was one of the most inspirational experiences I have to this day in my pursuit of music.

Now, many years later, I’m beyond stoked to continue my journey learning from the best of the best. His training at Berklee and rigorous practice and undying passion for understanding guitar makes him pinnacle in the industry.

If you’re looking to truly improve yourself skills or even just learn the guitar, hit Brett up @inmybookofspells and give him a follow! Tell him I sent ya. ❤️🤘🏼

node.text:
Are you afraid? Good. 😈

Fear is the mind killer. But being afraid isn’t necessarily a thing to avoid entirely. 

Our fears help up understand the reality of the consequences we have to face from our actions. They give us an objective perspective of what is really required to pursue what we want in life. 

If you’re afraid, know that you’re one step closer to understanding your self, your boundaries, and your reality. However, don’t let all of your fears stop you from truly going after what you deserve. 

❤️

node.text:
Tetris gone Metal by Doctor P. 🎸🤘🏼 with @positivegrid Spark

Trying to switch things up with my tone. It’s been awesome playing with sounds with my Spark amp. Still have lots to learn, but I’m able to experiment with tones I would have never thought of on my own. It’s been a great learning experience.

Click the link in my bio to get $40 off your Spark now!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by KIKI WONG in Los Angeles, California with @officialjacksonguitars, and @akanet91. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.

node.text:
There are two things that will truly define you:
1) Patience when you have nothing 
2) Your attitude when you have everything

No matter how crazy life gets or how amazing things become, how much you win, how much you lose, don’t lose yourself in the process. 

Hang in there. Stay amazing. ❤️
